<paragraph id="90113690EC1DFFA5209CFE42BEA5FE56" blockId="4.[151,526,366,428]" box="[151,403,402,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">
<heading id="CB5981FCEC1DFFA5209CFE42BEA5FE56" bold="true" box="[151,403,402,428]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="421" reason="1">
<emphasis id="A2DAEA82EC1DFFA5209CFE42BEA5FE56" bold="true" box="[151,403,402,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">
<figureCitation id="08952A15EC1DFFA5209CFE42BE34FE56" box="[151,258,402,428]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="5.[151,250,1942,1966]" captionStartId-1="6.[151,250,1679,1703]" captionStartId-2="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox-0="[221,1367,188,1916]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,181,1655]" captionTargetBox-2="[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetId-0="figure-17@5.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetId-1="figure-17@6.[151,1436,181,1655]" captionTargetId-2="figure-17@7.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionTargetPageId-2="7" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Phylogenetic relationships of Oligodon melaneus.A) ML phylogeny with bootstrap support values, B) BI phylogeny with Bayesian posterior probability support values." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Designated lectotype of Oligodon melaneus (BMNH 1910.12.31.3). Photographs by Kevin Webb. Scale bar increments in mm." captionText-2="FIGURE 3. Paralectotype of Oligodon melaneus BNHS 958. Photographs by Saunak Pal. Image not to scale." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571656" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571658" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571660" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6571656/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6571658/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6571660/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
, 
<tableCitation id="DD2C032BEC1DFFA52105FE42BEB8FE56" box="[270,398,402,428]" captionStart-0="TABLE 1" captionStart-1="TABLE 2" captionStartId-0="2.[151,239,485,511]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,244,150,176]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionText-0="TABLE 1. GenBank accession and voucher numbers for the sequences used in this study." captionText-1="TABLE 2. Morphometric (in mm) and meristic data for the two previously known (type) specimens and the newly reported specimen of Oligodon melaneus. Counts are given in right, left order. “–“damaged scales. * on the right side, the 2nd and 3rd and (especially) the 6th and 7th supralabials are incompletely distinct (are partially ‘fused’). Values in square brackets are those reported by Wall (1909)." httpUri-0="http://table.plazi.org/id/C4D16618EC1BFFA3209CFE35BB63FE05" httpUri-1="http://table.plazi.org/id/C4D16618EC11FFA9209CFF46BC0FFEE7" pageId="4" pageNumber="421" tableUuid-0="C4D16618EC1BFFA3209CFE35BB63FE05" tableUuid-1="C4D16618EC11FFA9209CFF46BC0FFEE7">Tables 1–2</tableCitation>
.
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="90113690EC1DFFA5209CFE0ABEB9FD9A" blockId="4.[151,1437,474,1545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">
Wall (1909) provided relatively detailed descriptions of the 
<specimenCount id="86A8FD19EC1DFFA5235FFE0BBCD9FE0F" box="[852,1007,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
. We note differences between Wall’s and our observations in the text and 
<tableCitation id="DD2C032BEC1DFFA52239FE2EBDB1FDE2" box="[562,647,510,536]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,244,150,176]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 2. Morphometric (in mm) and meristic data for the two previously known (type) specimens and the newly reported specimen of Oligodon melaneus. Counts are given in right, left order. “–“damaged scales. * on the right side, the 2nd and 3rd and (especially) the 6th and 7th supralabials are incompletely distinct (are partially ‘fused’). Values in square brackets are those reported by Wall (1909)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/C4D16618EC11FFA9209CFF46BC0FFEE7" pageId="4" pageNumber="421" tableUuid="C4D16618EC11FFA9209CFF46BC0FFEE7">Table 2</tableCitation>
, and provide the first photographs of the 
<typeStatus id="4F158832EC1DFFA52450FE2FBB8BFDE3" box="[1115,1213,511,537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">syntypes</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="08952A15EC1DFFA524C6FE2EBA2DFDE2" box="[1229,1307,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1679,1703]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[151,1436,181,1655]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Designated lectotype of Oligodon melaneus (BMNH 1910.12.31.3). Photographs by Kevin Webb. Scale bar increments in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571658" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571658/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="08952A15EC1DFFA52559FE2EBA57FDE2" box="[1362,1377,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Paralectotype of Oligodon melaneus BNHS 958. Photographs by Saunak Pal. Image not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571660/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="421">3</figureCitation>
), but otherwise focus on a more detailed description of the new specimen because it was collected more than 
<quantity id="57569B75EC1DFFA5254EFDF2BAAAFDC6" box="[1349,1436,546,572]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="421" unit="km" value="260.0">260 km</quantity>
from the type locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
